<section
  id="insight"
  class="relative px-6 py-28 sm:px-10 lg:px-16 bg-[#16161f]"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center" data-aos="fade-up">
    <div class="mb-10 flex items-center justify-center gap-4" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="h-px w-16 bg-[#7c3aed]/40"></span>
      <span class="h-2 w-2 rotate-45 bg-[#7c3aed]"></span>
      <span class="h-px w-16 bg-[#7c3aed]/40"></span>
    </div>

    <h2
      class="text-3xl font-semibold italic tracking-tight text-[#f0f0f6] sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl"
    >
      Power without coordination is noise.
    </h2>

    <p
      class="mx-auto mt-8 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#9090a8]"
      data-aos="fade-up"
      data-aos-delay="100"
    >
      Individual AI tooling is zero-sum. Ten developers each iterating on their
      own prompts produces ten versions of the same wheel — and zero compounding
      gains. The teams pulling ahead aren't the ones with smarter models.
      They're the ones with a shared layer underneath. Like a git history for
      prompts: everyone contributes, everyone inherits.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
